8251	[Push--pull over the {\v C}ech backbone is the product over intersection opens]
8252	  \label{lem:pushPull_sigma_iso}
8253	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.pushPull_sigma_iso}
8254	  \uses{def:push_pull_obj, lem:cech_backbone_left_sigma, lem:pushPull_coprod_prod}
8255	  With the notation of Lemma~\ref{lem:cech_backbone_left_sigma}, the push--pull object on
8256	  the degree-\(p\) backbone decomposes as a product over the multi-indices:
8257	  \[
8258	    \operatorname{pushPullObj}\mathcal{F}\,Y_p
8259	      \;\cong\;
8260	    \prod_{\sigma : \mathrm{Fin}(p+1) \to I}
8261	      \operatorname{pushPullObj}\mathcal{F}\,(\operatorname{Over.mk} j_\sigma)
8262	    \qquad \text{in } X.\mathrm{Modules},
8263	  \]
8264	  equivalently \((q_p)_*\,(q_p)^*\mathcal{F} \cong \prod_\sigma (j_\sigma)_*\,
8265	  (j_\sigma)^*\mathcal{F}\).
8266	\end{lemma}
8267	\begin{proof}
8268	  \uses{lem:cech_backbone_left_sigma, lem:pushPull_coprod_prod}
8269	  By Lemma~\ref{lem:cech_backbone_left_sigma} the backbone \(Y_p\) is the coproduct
8270	  \(\coprod_\sigma U_\sigma\) with structure map \(q_p = \operatorname{Sigma.desc}(\sigma
8271	  \mapsto j_\sigma)\). Apply Lemma~\ref{lem:pushPull_coprod_prod} to this coproduct family,
8272	  with the finite multi-index type \(\sigma : \mathrm{Fin}(p+1) \to I\) as the index and the
8273	  intersection-open legs \(\operatorname{Over.mk} j_\sigma\), to obtain the asserted product
8274	  decomposition.
8275	\end{proof}
